The paper deals with the space complexity of single-pass streaming algorithms for approximating the set cover problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in terms of analyzing the space complexity of the algorithms. The problem of set cover is closely related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper involves machine learning (cs.LG) techniques in terms of designing the algorithms.
